As the vortices move closer to the plate, the pressure loading on the plate increases in magnitude in concert with the plate deflection (see Figure 3(b)). When the vortex pair is very near the plate (see Figure 3(c)), the pressure loading magnitude increases dramatically at the x location on the plate corresponding to 


ℜ
